## Partitioning (optional, not enabled by default)

This project initialized as **Generic**, which defaults to a single `developer` agent (`.harness/agents/developer.md`).

If the project becomes large enough that partitioned developers would help, ask AI to:

1. Identify natural partition boundaries (e.g. `dev-mobile-ios` + `dev-mobile-android` for a mobile app; `dev-data-pipeline` + `dev-data-api` for an ML project; `dev-rust` + `dev-react` for a Tauri app)
2. Create `.harness/agents/dev-<name>.md` for each partition with explicit owned-paths globs
3. Update this file (or a new `55-partitioning.md`) to document the partitioning scheme
4. Run `.harness/scripts/harness-sync` to copy the new agent files to `.claude/agents/`
5. Update `AI-GUIDE.md`'s "Agents" section to list the new partitions

The Solution Architect, when partition agents exist, must produce a partition-assignment table in `02_SOLUTION_DESIGN.md` for any task that touches multiple partitions.

## Stack-specific verify_all checks (optional)

If your stack has properties worth verifying beyond build / test / lint, add steps to `.harness/scripts/verify_all.{ps1,sh}`. Examples:

- Rust: `cargo audit` for security
- Python: `pip-audit` or `safety check`
- Node: `pnpm audit --audit-level=high`
- Any: spell-check on user-facing strings, license header on source files, ...
